# @psyforge/headless

WebAssembly-compiled ForgeScript runtime for high-performance simulation and testing of psychology experiments.

## Overview

The `@psyforge/headless` package provides a deterministic, high-speed simulation environment for ForgeScript experiments. It includes:

- **WebAssembly Runtime**: Executes experiments at 100x+ real-time speed
- **Cognitive Models**: Realistic participant response generation
- **Virtual Devices**: Hardware simulation without physical devices
- **Memory Management**: Strict budget enforcement (<100MB)
- **Performance Monitoring**: Real-time metrics and optimization

## Installation

```bash
npm install @psyforge/headless
```

## Quick Start

```typescript
import { HeadlessRunner, CognitiveModels } from '@psyforge/headless';
import { experiment } from './my-experiment';

// Configure simulation
const config = {
  experiment: experiment.compile(),
  cognitiveModel: CognitiveModels.stroopModel,
  participants: 30,
  speedMultiplier: 100, // 100x real-time
  randomSeed: 12345,    // For reproducibility
  memoryBudget: 50 * 1024 * 1024 // 50MB
};

// Run simulation
const runner = new HeadlessRunner(config);
const results = await runner.simulate();

// Analyze results
console.log(`Overall accuracy: ${results.aggregateMetrics.overallAccuracy}`);
console.log(`Mean RT: ${results.aggregateMetrics.overallMeanRT}ms`);
console.log(`Speedup: ${results.performanceReport.speedupFactor}x`);
```

## Cognitive Models

### Built-in Models

#### Simple Reaction Time
```typescript
import { CognitiveModels } from '@psyforge/headless';

const model = CognitiveModels.simpleRT;
// baseRT: 400ms, practiceEffect: 0.02, errorRate: 0.05
```

#### Stroop Task
```typescript
const model = CognitiveModels.stroopModel;
// congruentRT: 350ms, incongruentRT: 450ms
// Includes conflict adaptation effects
```

#### N-Back Working Memory
```typescript
const model = CognitiveModels.nBackModel;
// Simulates working memory capacity limits
// Adjusts accuracy based on n-back level
```

#### Visual Search
```typescript
const model = CognitiveModels.visualSearchModel;
// Serial vs parallel search
// Set size effects
```

### Custom Cognitive Models

```typescript
import { CognitiveModel } from '@psyforge/headless';

class CustomModel implements CognitiveModel {
  reactionTime(stimulus: any, difficulty: number): number {
    // Custom RT generation logic
    return 300 + difficulty * 200 + Math.random() * 50;
  }

  accuracy(stimulus: any, fatigue: number): boolean {
    // Custom accuracy logic
    return Math.random() > (0.1 + fatigue * 0.2);
  }

  learningCurve(trialNumber: number, condition: string): number {
    // Custom learning effect
    return 1 - 0.1 * (1 - Math.exp(-trialNumber / 30));
  }
}
```

## Virtual Devices

### Virtual Keyboard
```typescript
import { VirtualDeviceFactory } from '@psyforge/headless';

const keyboard = VirtualDeviceFactory.createKeyboard({
  latency: 5,              // 5ms average latency
  keyPressVariability: 10, // ±10ms variability
  doublePressThreshold: 50 // Ignore presses within 50ms
});

// Simulate key press
const press = keyboard.simulateKeyPress('a', timestamp);
console.log(`Key pressed at ${press.timestamp} with ${press.latency}ms latency`);
```

### Virtual Mouse
```typescript
const mouse = VirtualDeviceFactory.createMouse({
  movementNoise: 2,     // ±2px jitter
  clickVariability: 5,  // ±5ms click timing
  scrollSensitivity: 3  // Scroll multiplier
});

// Simulate smooth movement
const path = mouse.simulateMovement(targetX, targetY, duration);
```

### Virtual Eye Tracker
```typescript
const eyeTracker = VirtualDeviceFactory.createEyeTracker({
  samplingRate: 250,      // Hz
  spatialAccuracy: 0.5,   // degrees
  fixationMinDuration: 100 // ms
});

// Simulate gaze path with saccade
const gazePath = eyeTracker.simulateGazePath(x1, y1, x2, y2);

// Simulate smooth pursuit
const pursuit = eyeTracker.simulateSmoothPursuit(movingTargetPath);
```

### Virtual EEG
```typescript
const eeg = VirtualDeviceFactory.createEEG({
  channels: 32,
  samplingRate: 500,        // Hz
  noiseFloor: 5,           // μV
  artifactProbability: 0.01 // 1% artifacts
});

// Generate EEG signal with events
const signal = eeg.generateSignal(duration, eventTimestamps);

// Generate specific ERP components
const p300 = eeg.generateERP('P300', amplitude);
```

## Time-Travel Simulation

Run experiments to specific time points for debugging:

```typescript
const runner = new HeadlessRunner(config);

// Simulate to 30 seconds
const state = await runner.simulateUntil(30);

console.log(`Current trial: ${state.currentTrial}`);
console.log(`Participant fatigue: ${state.participantState.fatigue}`);
console.log(`Memory usage: ${state.performanceMetrics.memoryUsage.wasmMemoryUsed}`);
```

## Performance Optimization

### Memory Management
```typescript
// Monitor memory usage
const memory = runner.getMemoryUsage();
if (memory.wasmMemoryUsed > memory.wasmMemoryLimit * 0.8) {
  console.warn('Approaching memory limit!');
}
```

### Speed Configuration
```typescript
// Balance speed vs accuracy
const config = {
  speedMultiplier: 1000,  // 1000x for quick validation
  // or
  speedMultiplier: 10,    // 10x for detailed analysis
};
```

## Data Export

Results are exported in BIDS-compatible format:

```typescript
const results = await runner.simulate();

// BIDS format data
results.dataExport.forEach(trial => {
  console.log({
    participant_id: trial.participant_id,
    trial: trial.trial,
    condition: trial.condition,
    rt: trial.rt,
    accuracy: trial.accuracy,
    onset: trial.onset,
    duration: trial.duration
  });
});

// Aggregate metrics
console.log(results.aggregateMetrics.conditionEffects);
console.log(results.aggregateMetrics.learningCurve);
console.log(results.aggregateMetrics.fatigueEffects);
```

## Advanced Usage

### Deterministic Simulation
```typescript
// Same seed = same results
const config1 = { randomSeed: 42, ...otherConfig };
const config2 = { randomSeed: 42, ...otherConfig };

const results1 = await new HeadlessRunner(config1).simulate();
const results2 = await new HeadlessRunner(config2).simulate();
// results1 and results2 will be identical
```

### Custom Analysis
```typescript
const results = await runner.simulate();

// Analyze individual participants
results.participants.forEach(participant => {
  const summary = participant.summary;
  console.log(`Participant ${participant.participantId}:`);
  console.log(`  Accuracy: ${summary.accuracy}`);
  console.log(`  Mean RT: ${summary.meanRT}ms (SD: ${summary.sdRT})`);
  console.log(`  Fastest: ${summary.minRT}ms, Slowest: ${summary.maxRT}ms`);
});

// Performance report
const report = results.performanceReport;
console.log(`Simulation took ${report.totalSimulationTime}ms real time`);
console.log(`Simulated ${report.virtualTimeElapsed}ms virtual time`);
console.log(`Speedup factor: ${report.speedupFactor}x`);
```

## Testing

```bash
# Run tests
npm test

# Coverage report
npm run test:coverage
```

## License

MIT

